{
  "doc_id": "9285",
  "text": "On the other hand, a transformation T is called linear if it has two mathematical properties: (a) additivity (T(x + y) = T(x) + T(y)) and (b) homogeneity (T(αx) = αT(x)). The linear transform domain features are very effective when the patterns are characterized by their spectral properties; so, here, we investigate the feature extraction capability of the discrete fourier transform (DFT), the discrete cosine transform and the Haar transform (HT) [CITATION_1] .",
